WEBVTT

00:30.297 --> 00:33.232
- Sally, uh...

00:33.234 --> 00:36.802
shopped at a co-op.

00:36.804 --> 00:38.704
She made her own ice cream.

00:42.576 --> 00:44.243
She went all over the world,

00:44.245 --> 00:47.112
and she helped people
every single day of her life.

00:50.418 --> 00:52.684
She gave that life for us.

00:52.686 --> 00:54.053
Let's not forget it.

00:54.055 --> 00:57.122
[rumbling]

00:57.124 --> 00:59.425
- That's just Mount Rainier.
We get it all the time.

00:59.427 --> 01:01.293
<i> [woman vocalizing]</i>

01:01.295 --> 01:04.196
[rumbling continues]

01:06.700 --> 01:10.836
- Yeah, you'd like that.

01:13.140 --> 01:16.075
[fire whooshing]

01:23.217 --> 01:26.185
<i> [somber music]</i>

01:26.187 --> 01:33.158
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:49.844 --> 01:52.778
[rumbling]

01:57.618 --> 02:01.220
- Is Mom gonna be okay?

02:01.222 --> 02:02.588
- I don't know.

02:04.225 --> 02:07.192
<i> [ominous music]</i>

02:07.194 --> 02:14.133
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:15.436 --> 02:17.402
- Guys, come on.
I'm fine.

02:17.404 --> 02:19.638
- I know, that's the weird part.

02:19.640 --> 02:20.906
- Hey, Karen, listen.

02:20.908 --> 02:22.191
I'm thinking
that it might be wise-

02:22.192 --> 02:23.475
- You want to go home.
We have Brianna.

02:23.477 --> 02:24.843
You want to go home.

02:24.845 --> 02:26.311
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

02:26.313 --> 02:27.913
- That's what I'm thinking.
- Me too.

02:27.915 --> 02:30.215
- Hey, I want you to stay.

02:30.217 --> 02:32.217
After the way the whole family
fought last night,

02:32.219 --> 02:34.353
I know you're up to it,
and you'll be safe.

02:34.355 --> 02:35.654
- It's the end of the world.
Nobody's safe.

02:35.656 --> 02:36.878
- Well, if you're gonna die,

02:36.879 --> 02:38.101
you may as well be
around your friends.

02:38.102 --> 02:39.324
- Nobody's gonna die.
We're not gonna die.

02:39.326 --> 02:41.193
You're not gonna die.
- Okay, okay.

02:41.195 --> 02:42.394
- Jesus.
- But if you're gonna leave,

02:42.396 --> 02:43.595
you need food and fuel.

02:43.597 --> 02:44.897
- You've given us enough.
- I've got both.

02:44.899 --> 02:46.298
- No, no, we're going
to Camp Keewatin.

02:46.300 --> 02:47.466
That's where Dana
was a counselor.

02:47.468 --> 02:48.800
We're gonna get
all our supplies there.

02:48.802 --> 02:51.336
- Oh, yeah, yeah,
that summer that I was away.

02:51.338 --> 02:53.205
- You were always away.
- Well, I was on a dig.

02:53.207 --> 02:54.506
I mean, that's part
of the job requirements.

02:54.508 --> 02:55.941
- I know, honey, I know.

02:55.943 --> 02:59.811
- I'll throw in a couple
extra shooters and a vehicle.

02:59.813 --> 03:01.680
- I don't want your shooters.
- Like hell you don't.

03:01.682 --> 03:03.215
I'm gonna
get my vehicle back.

03:03.217 --> 03:04.283
- What's the matter
with this guy?

03:04.285 --> 03:06.785
- Pride is a deadly sin, Booty.

03:06.787 --> 03:08.654
Take something from me for once.

03:13.661 --> 03:15.427
- She'll take it.
- I'll take it.

03:15.429 --> 03:17.329
Where are you gonna be?

03:17.331 --> 03:20.832
- I have to go get supplies
of my own.

03:20.834 --> 03:22.734
I have to go
to Memphis Pacific College.

03:22.736 --> 03:25.504
It's probably 25 miles
east of here.

03:25.506 --> 03:26.905
You remember Gloria Douglas?

03:26.907 --> 03:28.574
- The crazy professor?
- That's right.

03:28.576 --> 03:29.908
- How do you know
she's gonna be there?

03:29.910 --> 03:31.276
- No, everything
she predicted has come true,

03:31.278 --> 03:32.578
and I don't know
if she's gonna be there,

03:32.580 --> 03:33.879
but I know that they'll have
archived her work

03:33.881 --> 03:34.947
wherever she taught.

03:34.949 --> 03:36.248
So I'll just go to the college,

03:36.250 --> 03:37.649
and I'll meet you
at the camp after.

03:37.651 --> 03:38.951
- So you're gonna go through
all this danger

03:38.953 --> 03:40.385
just for some research?

03:40.387 --> 03:42.788
- Lamar, you're helping us
survive today.

03:42.790 --> 03:44.856
I'm trying to help us
survive tomorrow.

03:44.858 --> 03:47.459
- You're not going alone.

03:47.461 --> 03:48.527
- Okay, I'll take Briana
and Devyn.

03:48.529 --> 03:49.661
You take Dana and Matt.

03:49.663 --> 03:51.597
- Plus an additional
shooter per vehicle.

03:51.599 --> 03:53.465
Come on, Booty.
I got to do this.

03:53.467 --> 03:54.833
- Done.
- Deal.

03:54.835 --> 03:55.834
- Oh.

03:57.538 --> 03:58.670
- Done.

04:08.849 --> 04:10.449
- Here you go.

04:10.451 --> 04:12.317
- Your boyfriend's
in the back talking to himself.

04:12.319 --> 04:14.253
- Relax, Jane, hop in.
- He's praying, Matt.

04:16.624 --> 04:17.756
- [sighs]
Matt.

04:17.758 --> 04:19.725
[clears throat]
Listen, you're in charge

04:19.727 --> 04:20.759
of your mother.

04:20.761 --> 04:21.793
- She's gonna love that.

04:21.795 --> 04:22.961
- No, no, just don't
tell her that.

04:22.963 --> 04:26.031
Just observe and react.

04:26.033 --> 04:28.467
Stay close to her.

04:28.469 --> 04:31.036
- All right.

04:31.038 --> 04:32.004
- Here, grab hold.

04:32.006 --> 04:33.338
- Thanks.

04:44.518 --> 04:46.918
- That wasn't the best morning.

04:46.920 --> 04:49.421
- You can't dwell
on these things.

04:49.423 --> 04:50.989
- Yeah, I guess.
- I'm serious.

04:50.991 --> 04:51.990
We get distracted, we die.

04:51.992 --> 04:53.425
Got it?
- Yeah.

04:53.427 --> 04:56.061
- So you keep your eye
on the woods, not on me,

04:56.063 --> 04:59.431
in spite of what
your father said.

04:59.433 --> 05:02.634
- How did you know?
- I know your father.

05:02.636 --> 05:04.069
Be sharp.

05:04.071 --> 05:07.072
We're not the only ones
looking for supplies out there.

05:07.074 --> 05:09.041
[car engine turns over]

05:14.348 --> 05:16.748
- It's good to get going.

05:16.750 --> 05:18.850
- Of course she waited
for my dad to go first

05:18.852 --> 05:21.453
so she could watch him
for a while.

05:23.691 --> 05:26.792
Ooh, oops.

05:26.794 --> 05:27.959
- No problem.

05:30.898 --> 05:32.397
- Oh, sorry.

05:32.399 --> 05:34.566
I don't know
what's wrong with me.

05:34.568 --> 05:35.967
- Not much, in my opinion.

05:47.715 --> 05:50.549
- Godspeed, Booty.

05:50.551 --> 05:52.084
See you after the end.

05:52.086 --> 05:53.852
- You're the man, Lamar.

05:55.723 --> 05:57.823
- See you, Booner.

05:57.825 --> 05:59.925
- All right!
Lock it up!

06:01.795 --> 06:03.929
- All right, Dr. Douglas'
research is archived here.

06:03.931 --> 06:05.314
I won't be long.

06:05.315 --> 06:06.698
- Dad, how could she have
predicted all this shit?

06:06.700 --> 06:09.000
- I don't know.
I thought she was crazy, but--

06:09.002 --> 06:10.869
- I'm going with you.
- No, Dana, I want you

06:10.871 --> 06:13.438
with Bri and Devyn.

06:26.687 --> 06:29.888
- All right, let's load up
as fast as we can.

06:29.890 --> 06:31.723
Where do we find things?

06:31.725 --> 06:33.492
- Bulk food in the mess hall
and the kitchen.

06:33.494 --> 06:35.026
- Dry goods?
Survival?

06:35.028 --> 06:36.928
- They stored that
in the counselor's cabin.

06:36.930 --> 06:40.465
I know where that is.
- Okay, go with Martin.

06:40.467 --> 06:42.501
- Assume it's a free-fire zone.
Safeties off.

06:42.503 --> 06:44.569
- Don't sorry, Mrs. Copeland.
I got her.

06:47.975 --> 06:49.141
- Nothing bad's ever happened
to two young,

06:49.143 --> 06:50.409
sexy kids at a camp
before, right?

06:50.411 --> 06:53.044
- Stop it.

06:53.046 --> 06:56.715
- So this was your summer camp?
- Yeah, I loved it.

06:56.717 --> 06:58.984
Dark skies. You could see
the double star in Lyra,

06:58.986 --> 07:00.185
naked eye.

07:00.187 --> 07:02.487
- Wow.
Party girl.

07:02.489 --> 07:03.989
- [laughs]

07:03.991 --> 07:07.025
Well, plus I couldn't wait
to get away from my family.

07:07.027 --> 07:09.127
Seems funny to say that now.

07:09.129 --> 07:11.563
I fought with Brianna
all the time.

07:11.565 --> 07:13.665
- Over?
- The important stuff.

07:13.667 --> 07:15.567
Chores and clothes.

07:17.771 --> 07:19.471
- I was the only kid.

07:19.473 --> 07:21.673
I used to wish I had
a brother to fight with.

07:21.675 --> 07:24.709
- Well,
where are your parents now?

07:24.711 --> 07:27.612
- I'm from Seattle.

07:27.614 --> 07:29.481
- I'm sorry.

07:30.784 --> 07:33.718
- Where do 3 million people go?

07:33.720 --> 07:35.821
- I don't know.

07:35.823 --> 07:37.589
Somewhere good maybe.

07:39.960 --> 07:42.561
- I never thought of that.

07:42.563 --> 07:45.096
Something to hope for.

07:45.098 --> 07:47.699
- Hope is really all
that's left, I guess.

07:49.470 --> 07:52.237
<i> [ominous music]</i>

07:52.239 --> 07:54.539
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:54.541 --> 07:57.509
- You hear anything?
- Thought I heard an engine.

07:57.511 --> 08:00.111
- Someone at the camp?

08:00.113 --> 08:02.681
- Let's say hello.

08:02.683 --> 08:09.654
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:13.827 --> 08:15.494
- [sighs]

08:18.899 --> 08:21.066
- Damn, it's thick in here.

08:21.068 --> 08:22.734
- Stop your bitching!

08:22.736 --> 08:24.536
Come on, let's go this way.

08:24.538 --> 08:30.175
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:30.177 --> 08:31.276
- Found much more?

08:31.278 --> 08:32.711
- No, we emptied the kitchen.
- Great.

08:32.712 --> 08:34.145
- There are people out there.
- What people?

08:34.147 --> 08:35.514
- GRs in the woods.

08:35.516 --> 08:36.815
Two of them now,
but there could be more.

08:36.817 --> 08:37.949
- Where's Dana?

08:37.951 --> 08:40.185
- I don't know,
but they're armed.

08:40.187 --> 08:42.020
- Let's split up and find her.

08:47.861 --> 08:49.528
- [sighs]

08:49.530 --> 08:50.595
<i> - Put the knife on the table.</i>

08:50.597 --> 08:51.796
<i> [ominous music]</i>

08:51.798 --> 08:54.733
<i>- Ponga el cuchillo en la mesa.</i>

08:54.735 --> 08:56.735
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:56.737 --> 08:59.271
<i> - Would you like some water?</i>

08:59.273 --> 09:02.807
<i> - Quieres agua?</i>

09:02.809 --> 09:06.578
<i> - Can you tell me</i>
<i> where the restroom is?</i>

09:06.580 --> 09:11.850
<i> - Puedes decirme dónde está</i>
<i> el baño?</i>

09:11.852 --> 09:15.820
<i> - I would like to purchase</i>
<i> some shoe polish.</i>

09:15.822 --> 09:19.891
<i> - Me gustaría comprar</i>
<i> un poco de betún.</i>

09:19.893 --> 09:23.128
<i>- This concludes Conversational</i>
<i> Spanish, lesson six.</i>

09:23.130 --> 09:24.095
[tape deck clicks]

09:24.097 --> 09:30.135
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:30.137 --> 09:32.070
- Dr. Douglas?

09:32.072 --> 09:33.605
Gloria Douglas?

09:33.607 --> 09:35.040
- Yes.

09:37.010 --> 09:38.176
- Hi.

09:38.178 --> 09:40.278
I'm Joshua Copeland.
Dr. Copeland.

09:40.280 --> 09:42.314
- Oh.

09:42.316 --> 09:44.049
What brings you here?

09:44.051 --> 09:45.216
- Well, to be honest with you,

09:45.218 --> 09:47.686
I was looking
for your dissertation.

09:47.688 --> 09:49.821
- Of course.
- You remember me?

09:49.823 --> 09:52.223
- Sure, you're Joshua Copeland.

09:52.225 --> 09:55.594
- Yeah, from Whitstron College.

09:55.596 --> 09:57.128
I, uh, I think
I was opposed to your work

09:57.130 --> 09:58.663
when you first put it out,

09:58.664 --> 10:00.197
and I think we had
some very bitter words,

10:00.200 --> 10:02.067
which I was wrong.

10:02.069 --> 10:05.770
I think your work is filled
with important insights.

10:05.772 --> 10:08.373
- Of course.

10:08.375 --> 10:10.609
- I didn't expect to run
into you in person.

10:10.611 --> 10:14.646
I'm glad that I have
an opportunity to say I'm sorry,

10:14.648 --> 10:16.948
ask you if I could
maybe re-read your work.

10:20.287 --> 10:23.722
- Well, you're having a good day
then, aren't you?

10:36.703 --> 10:39.738
- Wow, you're a fast stacker.

10:39.740 --> 10:42.140
- Yeah, it's one of
my better qualities.

10:42.142 --> 10:44.009
It's not my best.
- [chuckles]

10:48.315 --> 10:50.081
Okay, we are going to talk.

10:50.083 --> 10:51.683
- Yeah, I think the odds
on that are long.

10:51.685 --> 10:53.218
- We need to find out everything
about each other,

10:53.220 --> 10:54.886
and there is very little time.

10:54.888 --> 10:56.388
- Okay, you first.

10:56.390 --> 10:58.256
- Okay, I almost never
wear makeup.

10:58.258 --> 10:59.858
- Me either.

10:59.860 --> 11:02.327
- But I am surprisingly
good at walking in heels.

11:02.329 --> 11:03.962
- Me too.

11:03.964 --> 11:06.064
- I think you're just saying
anything that comes to mind

11:06.066 --> 11:08.400
in hopes of having sex with me.

11:08.402 --> 11:10.268
- I would never do that.

11:10.270 --> 11:12.003
Except for right now,

11:12.005 --> 11:13.905
and any other time we're both
in the state of Washington.

11:13.907 --> 11:15.674
- Or a state of undress.

11:15.676 --> 11:19.711
Sorry, sorry,
that just came out.

11:19.713 --> 11:22.714
- Yeah, are we really
gonna do this?

11:22.716 --> 11:25.884
- Yeah, the evidence
says we are, yeah.

11:25.886 --> 11:30.155
- Because I just got to say,
and I swear it's the last time,

11:30.157 --> 11:31.356
I'm a lot older than you,

11:31.358 --> 11:33.191
and I'm your bodyguard, and--

11:33.193 --> 11:35.226
- Martin.
Martin.

11:35.228 --> 11:39.297
What you are is someone
I am really attracted to,

11:39.299 --> 11:43.334
and normally--normally we would
just take a beat

11:43.336 --> 11:44.836
and figure this out,

11:44.838 --> 11:48.173
but the world
is probably ending.

11:48.175 --> 11:49.874
- Yeah, I know, but--

11:49.876 --> 11:52.877
- And you can't regret
what you won't live to regret.

11:56.216 --> 11:57.182
- You got a point.

11:57.184 --> 11:58.817
- [laughs]

12:00.420 --> 12:01.720
[both sigh]

12:22.476 --> 12:25.210
- [gasps]

12:25.212 --> 12:26.244
- What's wrong?

12:26.246 --> 12:28.813
- Go away, please.

12:36.289 --> 12:37.822
- I'm back here if you need me.

12:40.060 --> 12:43.027
<i> [ominous music]</i>

12:43.029 --> 12:49.968
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:56.376 --> 12:59.077
- Did you find it yet?

12:59.079 --> 13:01.079
- No.
- Why is it so important to you?

13:01.081 --> 13:03.915
- Why? 'Cause everything
you wrote is coming true.

13:03.917 --> 13:06.451
Comets, plagues, skinwalkers,
even the mythic beasts.

13:06.453 --> 13:08.086
- Indeed.

13:08.088 --> 13:10.455
- So if you can predict
what's gonna happen next...

13:10.457 --> 13:11.456
- Let me show you.

13:11.458 --> 13:13.825
<i> [intense music]</i>

13:13.827 --> 13:15.527
[growling]

13:17.430 --> 13:18.797
<i> [intense music]</i>

13:18.799 --> 13:21.366
- [growling]

13:21.368 --> 13:28.306
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:29.376 --> 13:33.111
[yelling]

13:33.113 --> 13:34.112
[gunshot]

13:34.114 --> 13:35.146
[exclaiming]

13:35.148 --> 13:38.116
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

13:38.118 --> 13:40.552
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:40.554 --> 13:42.237
- What the hell is that?

13:42.238 --> 13:43.921
- Where did you come from?
- I hadn't seen you in a bit,

13:43.924 --> 13:46.057
and in Booner's system
it's hands on every ten minutes.

13:46.059 --> 13:48.059
- Thank God for Booner.
- I say it again,

13:48.061 --> 13:49.527
what the hell is that?
- It's a Fetch.

13:49.529 --> 13:51.062
It's an Anglo-Saxon word
for shape-shifter.

13:51.064 --> 13:52.497
- Uh-huh.

13:52.498 --> 13:53.931
- I mean, they have them in
every culture and every legend,

13:53.934 --> 13:55.934
but they can turn into
anyone you know,

13:55.936 --> 13:57.268
and then they become murderous.

13:57.270 --> 13:59.003
At least that's the legend.

13:59.005 --> 14:00.305
- Like we don't have
enough shit already.

14:00.307 --> 14:03.274
- Something else that
Dr. Douglas predicted,

14:03.276 --> 14:05.510
which means if it
can turn into her,

14:05.512 --> 14:08.413
then she's in the vicinity.

14:08.415 --> 14:10.114
We have to find her.

14:10.116 --> 14:12.417
- Well, this is an archive.

14:12.419 --> 14:14.485
You'd think her address
is in here somewhere.

14:14.487 --> 14:18.189
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:18.191 --> 14:20.225
- [laughing]
Stop tickling me.

14:20.227 --> 14:23.328
- What?

14:23.330 --> 14:25.330
- Stop it.

14:25.332 --> 14:26.331
[screaming]

14:26.333 --> 14:27.465
- Dana!

14:27.467 --> 14:28.433
Hold on!
- Help!

14:28.435 --> 14:29.567
Help me!

14:29.569 --> 14:31.035
[yelling]
- [grunts]

14:31.037 --> 14:32.170
- [yells]
Get it off!

14:32.172 --> 14:33.304
- Get off!

14:33.306 --> 14:34.305
- [yells]
Please!

14:34.307 --> 14:35.573
- Almost!
Almost!

14:35.575 --> 14:37.375
- [yelling]
Get it off!

14:37.377 --> 14:38.977
- [grunts]
Go on!

14:38.979 --> 14:40.078
Go, go!

14:40.080 --> 14:41.179
Go, go, go!

14:41.181 --> 14:42.213
Come on.

14:42.215 --> 14:43.982
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

14:43.984 --> 14:45.250
Oh, shit, I left my gun.

14:45.252 --> 14:46.317
- Don't bother.

14:46.319 --> 14:49.554
- We got the only ones
you'll need.

14:49.556 --> 14:51.189
- What are you all doing here?

14:53.894 --> 14:55.526
- This is our camp, okay?

14:55.528 --> 14:57.996
And we don't like
uninvited guests.

14:57.998 --> 15:00.598
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:00.600 --> 15:04.402
- Look, we don't know you guys
and you don't know us,

15:04.404 --> 15:06.404
but I need to warn you.

15:06.406 --> 15:07.939
- [whispering]
Dana, don't.

15:07.941 --> 15:09.641
- [whispering]
I have to.

15:11.177 --> 15:12.911
That vine around your leg,

15:12.913 --> 15:14.312
there's a killer plant
underneath that cabin,

15:14.314 --> 15:18.149
and it's gonna pull you
underground and eat you.

15:18.151 --> 15:19.317
- Nice try.
[gun cocks]

15:19.319 --> 15:20.318
<i> [intense music]</i>

15:20.320 --> 15:22.120
- [screams]

15:22.122 --> 15:24.155
Jessie, it's got me!
- Let's get out of here!

15:24.157 --> 15:25.957
- Help me, Jessie!
It's got me!

15:25.959 --> 15:27.659
[screaming]

15:27.661 --> 15:30.061
Help!
It's eating me!

15:30.063 --> 15:31.329
Kill me!

15:31.331 --> 15:33.998
[gunfire]

15:34.000 --> 15:36.401
<i> [tense music]</i>

15:36.403 --> 15:39.203
- [sobbing]

15:39.205 --> 15:40.255
- What the hell?

15:40.256 --> 15:41.306
- That was Jess.
I know her voice.

15:41.308 --> 15:42.974
- Okay, let's go.

15:42.976 --> 15:46.678
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:46.680 --> 15:50.248
<i> [jazz music playing on radio]</i>

15:50.250 --> 15:52.116
- Do you really have
to listen to that?

15:52.118 --> 15:54.218
- There's nothing else on.

15:54.220 --> 15:56.321
- Well, hep talk from the '50s
isn't gonna help us.

15:56.323 --> 15:57.455
- Well, it can't hurt.

15:57.457 --> 15:59.223
<i> - Water above and fire below,</i>

15:59.225 --> 16:01.159
<i> the next wave's got</i>
<i> a bubbling glow,</i>

16:01.161 --> 16:03.094
<i> and the next precip</i>
<i> is some kind of tip</i>

16:03.096 --> 16:05.163
<i> with hot rocks</i>
<i> from deeper down the roads.</i>

16:05.165 --> 16:06.664
<i>Won't be rain when it explodes,</i>

16:06.666 --> 16:09.300
<i> it'll be Rainier</i>
<i> if you'll pardon my eruption.</i>

16:09.302 --> 16:10.668
- Mount Rainier?
<i> - And what happens</i>

16:10.670 --> 16:12.570
<i> when the underground</i>
<i> leaves dark behind</i>

16:12.572 --> 16:14.005
<i> and burns out bright?</i>

16:14.007 --> 16:16.040
<i> I don't think this thing</i>
<i> blows tonight,</i>

16:16.042 --> 16:17.508
<i> but soon, aficionados, soon.</i>

16:17.510 --> 16:20.044
- Is he talking
about Mount Rainier erupting?

16:20.046 --> 16:22.213
- I don't know what he's talking
about. I just like the sound.

16:22.215 --> 16:25.083
- Ugh.

16:25.085 --> 16:29.253
The only address they have
for her is here at this college.

16:29.255 --> 16:31.222
She must have had her
mail forwarded.

16:31.224 --> 16:34.993
- Maybe she lives here,
like that shape-shifter thing.

16:34.995 --> 16:36.194
Why don't you
check this building,

16:36.196 --> 16:38.997
I'll check the residences,
and meet back here?

16:38.999 --> 16:39.998
Let's go.

16:40.000 --> 16:41.532
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:49.042 --> 16:50.508
- [grunts]
- Mom!

16:50.510 --> 16:51.576
[sighs]

16:51.578 --> 16:54.012
- Don't do that to me.

16:54.014 --> 16:56.247
- I heard screaming and gunfire.

16:56.249 --> 16:57.582
I couldn't find her.

16:57.584 --> 16:59.550
- It's not Dana,
she's still here.

16:59.552 --> 17:02.520
Let's stick together,
scour the place.

17:02.522 --> 17:04.355
Try not to get shot.

17:06.192 --> 17:08.092
- Oh, no, no, no, no.

17:08.094 --> 17:10.361
[wails]

17:10.363 --> 17:12.130
[sobbing]

17:12.132 --> 17:14.399
It ate--
it ate her.

17:14.401 --> 17:15.800
We got to get out of here.

17:15.802 --> 17:17.201
- Who ate what?

17:17.203 --> 17:19.737
- The monster in this building,
it ate her.

17:19.739 --> 17:21.606
- Did you see the looters?
- Two.

17:21.608 --> 17:22.657
We had them cornered,

17:22.658 --> 17:23.707
and then they told us
about the monster,

17:23.710 --> 17:25.510
and then it took Roz.

17:25.512 --> 17:27.062
- Maybe they set a trap.

17:27.063 --> 17:28.613
- Yeah, with the monster
they carry around.

17:28.615 --> 17:30.715
Look, I don't know
who these people are,

17:30.717 --> 17:33.785
but they have to answer for Roz.

17:33.787 --> 17:35.253
Let's find them.

17:41.594 --> 17:43.127
- We can't just hide
in the woods.

17:43.129 --> 17:45.229
- Hey, hey,
they're looking for us.

17:45.231 --> 17:46.631
I'm unarmed, and we don't know
how many we're facing.

17:46.633 --> 17:48.299
- But Mom and Matt--

17:48.301 --> 17:51.702
- Have better odds if we don't
lead hostiles right to them.

17:51.704 --> 17:54.439
- What if--what if they find
Mom on their own?

17:54.441 --> 17:56.274
- Then...

17:56.276 --> 17:58.709
I pity the fool.

17:58.711 --> 18:01.612
Hey, it's gonna be okay.

18:01.614 --> 18:02.613
- I know.

18:04.317 --> 18:06.284
- Come on, let's go.

18:06.286 --> 18:09.253
<i> [ominous music]</i>

18:09.255 --> 18:10.788
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:10.790 --> 18:11.789
- Gloria?

18:11.791 --> 18:17.462
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:17.464 --> 18:19.797
Is it Gloria Douglas?

18:19.799 --> 18:26.404
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:26.406 --> 18:28.206
Dr. Douglas?

18:28.208 --> 18:32.777
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:32.779 --> 18:34.345
- Joshua Copeland.

18:34.347 --> 18:38.349
- Yes.
- It's me.

18:38.351 --> 18:41.319
Trust you to get past
the shape-shifter.

18:44.691 --> 18:46.457
- Was that a Fetch?

18:48.795 --> 18:51.429
- That's the
Anglo-Saxon version.

18:51.431 --> 18:55.733
I prefer to use
the Filipino word:

18:55.735 --> 18:57.435
Aswang.

18:57.437 --> 19:01.205
Kind of reminds me
of you somehow, Aswang.

19:01.207 --> 19:03.407
-<i> Y los demonios</i>
<i> va a surgir.</i>

19:03.409 --> 19:04.609
- And the sun will darken,

19:04.611 --> 19:06.644
and the demons will emerge.

19:06.646 --> 19:07.778
[tape deck clicks]

19:09.816 --> 19:11.582
Well, since we're
gonna die soon,

19:11.584 --> 19:13.351
let's say we have a drink.

19:17.657 --> 19:20.291
- Relax, the bourbon's
on the table..

19:20.293 --> 19:21.459
- How did you know
about the Fetch?

19:21.461 --> 19:23.594
- We call it an Aswang.

19:23.596 --> 19:28.432
Do not be such a WASP
about every little thing, Josh.

19:28.434 --> 19:30.735
[sighs]

19:30.737 --> 19:32.236
I'll get it.

19:35.175 --> 19:37.608
I was at my office last week
doing some work,

19:37.610 --> 19:39.877
and the thing
came slithering in.

19:39.879 --> 19:43.514
I think--I think it might be
some kind of virus.

19:43.516 --> 19:47.585
So they touch a crumb, a DNA,

19:47.587 --> 19:51.222
and they can use it
to replicate,

19:51.224 --> 19:53.758
and there they are.

19:53.760 --> 19:56.961
Or there you are.

19:56.963 --> 20:01.732
I even trained my Aswang to kill
anybody who came looking for me.

20:01.734 --> 20:03.801
- You trained a shape-shifter?

20:03.803 --> 20:06.637
- Just got to be smarter
than the virus, Josh.

20:08.508 --> 20:09.941
- How did you know?

20:09.943 --> 20:12.343
How did you know
all these things would appear?

20:12.345 --> 20:14.212
You wrote about them
even in your early work.

20:14.214 --> 20:15.379
- [chuckles]

20:15.381 --> 20:16.781
You mean the work
that you used to ruin me?

20:16.783 --> 20:18.282
That's what you want
to discuss right now

20:18.284 --> 20:20.618
in the last hours of your life?

20:20.620 --> 20:22.386
- The last hours of my life?

20:22.388 --> 20:25.323
- There've been 2,200
little earthquakes

20:25.325 --> 20:27.592
over the last 24 hours.

20:27.594 --> 20:29.527
It's called a swarm.
- I don't feel anything.

20:29.529 --> 20:32.363
- That's because
they stopped this morning,

20:32.365 --> 20:34.365
and that's a very
bad thing, Josh.

20:34.367 --> 20:37.001
This lovely institution lies

20:37.003 --> 20:39.637
in the shadow of Mount Rainier,
and you know what that means?

20:39.639 --> 20:43.274
That means that all those
little micro-vents,

20:43.276 --> 20:46.477
when the quakes happen,
they--they close.

20:46.479 --> 20:49.880
And when every single vent
gets shut tight,

20:49.882 --> 20:51.916
pressure starts to build,
and therefore what happens?

20:51.918 --> 20:53.918
What happens
when that happens?

20:53.920 --> 20:55.419
Boom.

20:55.421 --> 20:56.887
- Boom?

20:56.889 --> 20:58.623
- Boom.

20:58.625 --> 21:00.625
- When?

21:00.627 --> 21:01.959
- [sighs]

21:01.961 --> 21:03.427
I don't know.

21:03.429 --> 21:06.964
Sometime less than
the next 12 hours

21:06.966 --> 21:10.534
and more than the next
30 seconds, say.

21:10.536 --> 21:12.770
[sighs]

21:12.772 --> 21:14.438
I presume you want to leave now.

21:14.440 --> 21:15.840
- No, I don't.
I want to discuss your work.

21:15.842 --> 21:17.408
- [chuckles]

21:17.410 --> 21:20.945
You mean the work
that you blackballed me with?

21:22.415 --> 21:23.881
- All right.

21:25.618 --> 21:28.953
I'm truly sorry for the part
that I played in that.

21:28.955 --> 21:32.456
I, you know,
I didn't realize, obviously.

21:38.364 --> 21:40.798
- Fine.

21:40.800 --> 21:43.901
You're in luck
'cause I'm lonely.

21:43.903 --> 21:46.537
The only thing worse
than being lonely is being right

21:46.539 --> 21:48.639
and nobody knows it.

21:50.076 --> 21:53.010
- Except me.
- Yeah, except you.

21:53.012 --> 21:54.478
You're all I got.

21:54.480 --> 21:56.814
- Listen, I have to
ask you something.

21:56.816 --> 21:58.249
I heard these broadcasts.

21:58.250 --> 21:59.683
Seems like they're from
decades ago,

21:59.686 --> 22:02.553
but I'm starting to think he's
talking about current events.

22:02.555 --> 22:04.722
- Josh, you're gonna have
to give up on all these quaint,

22:04.724 --> 22:06.524
little ideas.

22:06.526 --> 22:10.061
Time and space, it's not all
that it's cracked up to be.

22:10.063 --> 22:15.066
Maybe this guy just knows things
before they happen, like me.

22:15.068 --> 22:17.435
Don't you know things
before they happen, Josh?

22:17.437 --> 22:19.103
- Yeah, some things
I know, but--

22:19.105 --> 22:20.504
- Do you want me to tell you?

22:20.506 --> 22:21.505
- Yes.

22:23.843 --> 22:25.476
- Okay, I will.

22:28.114 --> 22:30.081
Did you ever learn how to surf?

22:30.083 --> 22:31.482
- No, why?

22:31.484 --> 22:35.453
- It would be useful
to ride the waves.

22:35.455 --> 22:37.788
- But what waves?
- Those waves, idiot.

22:37.790 --> 22:39.390
Those waves.

22:39.392 --> 22:41.692
Those are the waves
that are making things happen,

22:41.694 --> 22:44.395
that are hitting us,
that are smashing us to bits.

22:44.397 --> 22:46.731
- What kind of waves?

22:46.733 --> 22:47.765
- I don't know.

22:47.767 --> 22:50.501
They're--it's a physics thing.

22:50.503 --> 22:53.471
Really it's,
I don't know,

22:53.473 --> 22:57.141
gravity or magnetic, or--

22:57.143 --> 23:01.545
oh, my God, I'm so tired.

23:01.547 --> 23:02.947
Well, that's all I got.

23:02.949 --> 23:04.415
It's a wave.

23:06.052 --> 23:08.486
- Can we do anything to stop it?

23:08.488 --> 23:09.620
- If I could stop it,

23:09.622 --> 23:10.888
would I be camped out

23:10.890 --> 23:13.858
in this archive
getting drunk every day?

23:13.860 --> 23:16.060
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:16.062 --> 23:18.162
How about another?

23:18.164 --> 23:25.136
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:34.013 --> 23:35.112
- This is where the camp
counselors

23:35.114 --> 23:36.714
would come to make out.

23:36.716 --> 23:38.015
- Huh, including you?

23:38.017 --> 23:39.984
- Yeah, with Marquise.

23:39.986 --> 23:41.786
- Who's he?

23:41.788 --> 23:45.723
- Beautiful eyes.
Big teeth.

23:45.725 --> 23:47.458
I like a guy
with big teeth, okay?

23:47.460 --> 23:49.160
[laughs]
- How are mine?

23:51.097 --> 23:52.763
- You have other qualities.

23:54.000 --> 23:55.166
- Come here.

23:55.168 --> 23:56.667
- [giggles]

24:00.139 --> 24:02.039
- Mm.

24:02.041 --> 24:04.942
[women speaking indistinctly]

24:04.944 --> 24:07.511
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:07.513 --> 24:09.780
- There ain't no monsters.
It's something else.

24:09.782 --> 24:12.716
- Something else like what?

24:12.718 --> 24:17.221
- Will you two just zip it
and keep your eyes open?

24:17.223 --> 24:20.090
- You see any tracks?
- Nothing yet.

24:20.092 --> 24:23.127
- They got to be
around here somewhere.

24:23.129 --> 24:24.995
- We'll find them.

24:27.099 --> 24:32.069
- So this, this wave, is it--

24:32.071 --> 24:33.804
does that control everything?

24:33.806 --> 24:36.140
- That is such a male thing
to say, controlled.

24:36.142 --> 24:38.742
No, of course the wave
doesn't control anything.

24:38.744 --> 24:41.078
It's like a man.
It doesn't have a mind.

24:41.080 --> 24:45.549
It's just a thing that causes
other things to happen.

24:45.551 --> 24:48.752
- Okay.
- Are you married?

24:48.754 --> 24:51.222
- Yes.
- I'm not married.

24:51.224 --> 24:52.857
I knew too much.

24:52.859 --> 24:54.625
- You're learning Spanish.

24:54.627 --> 24:56.594
- It's a bit late in the game,
I have to admit.

24:56.596 --> 24:57.995
It's a Spanish mystic,
Bartolomé.

24:57.997 --> 24:59.897
He died about 1,000 years ago,

24:59.899 --> 25:01.232
and it was reading his stuff

25:01.234 --> 25:03.501
that led me to investigate
all this other stuff.

25:03.503 --> 25:04.902
- Yeah, did he predict
these events?

25:04.904 --> 25:06.871
- No, but he probably would have

25:06.873 --> 25:08.539
if he hadn't been
burned at the stake.

25:08.541 --> 25:10.574
- So things described
in end-time prophesies

25:10.576 --> 25:11.575
from dozens
of different cultures

25:11.577 --> 25:12.810
are suddenly becoming real.

25:12.812 --> 25:14.111
- It's the damnedest thing,
isn't it?

25:14.113 --> 25:15.713
- So did this mystic,
did he have some insight

25:15.715 --> 25:18.416
into what's gonna happen next?

25:18.417 --> 25:21.118
- Sure, and it would kill
every drop of hope you have.

25:21.120 --> 25:23.187
- There's always hope.
- [chuckles]

25:23.189 --> 25:24.688
- What did he say?

25:24.690 --> 25:28.993
- He said,
"Everything ends forever."

25:32.265 --> 25:34.832
Did I happen to mention
that Mount Rainier's gonna blow?

25:34.834 --> 25:36.967
The most violent volcano
in the world,

25:36.969 --> 25:39.270
and we're sitting right
on top of it.

25:39.272 --> 25:41.605
- Yeah, well, Yellowstone
Caldera's on top of--

25:41.607 --> 25:45.042
- If I'd meant Caldera,
I would have said Caldera.

25:45.044 --> 25:48.779
It is the most
dangerous volcano in the world,

25:48.781 --> 25:50.915
and we are sitting right
on top of it.

25:50.917 --> 25:53.751
Plus, get this, the big headed
dopes that built this archive

25:53.753 --> 25:57.288
put it right on top
of this immense lava vent.

25:58.858 --> 26:01.659
- So Bob Black's broadcasts,
they're real.

26:01.661 --> 26:02.860
They're happening in real time.

26:02.862 --> 26:03.894
He's describing
what's really happening.

26:03.896 --> 26:05.262
He's describing Mount Rainier.

26:07.333 --> 26:09.133
So we need to get out of here.

26:09.135 --> 26:11.235
- You go.
I'm gonna stay.

26:11.237 --> 26:12.303
- Why is that?

26:12.305 --> 26:14.204
- Because...

26:14.206 --> 26:16.307
I'm trying to kill myself.

26:18.578 --> 26:23.781
I want to kill myself,
and I can't do it,

26:23.783 --> 26:27.117
so I'm gonna
let the volcano do it for me.

26:33.125 --> 26:35.025
- Look at me.

26:35.027 --> 26:37.194
- I want to get out of here.

26:37.196 --> 26:40.030
- I know, me too.

26:40.032 --> 26:42.166
Devyn, I promised
Jane we'd stay in--

26:42.168 --> 26:43.601
Devyn.

26:43.603 --> 26:44.602
Devyn.

26:44.604 --> 26:49.373
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:49.375 --> 26:51.008
Devyn!

26:51.010 --> 26:52.076
Devyn, what are you doing?

26:52.078 --> 26:54.078
- Nothing.

26:54.080 --> 26:56.747
Just go away
and I can do it.

26:56.749 --> 26:59.216
- Do what?

26:59.218 --> 27:00.818
Devyn, where are you?

27:04.056 --> 27:07.257
[whispering]
Where the hell are you?

27:07.259 --> 27:09.827
Devyn, talk to me.

27:13.899 --> 27:16.767
[leaves and twigs rustling]

27:21.040 --> 27:23.941
Devyn, I can tell you're moving.

27:23.943 --> 27:26.310
Devyn, come out.

27:28.714 --> 27:29.747
<i> [tense music]</i>

27:29.749 --> 27:32.116
[exhales sharply]
Oh, my God.

27:32.118 --> 27:34.985
Oh, my God.

27:34.987 --> 27:37.388
- I told you not to look.

27:37.390 --> 27:39.056
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:39.058 --> 27:42.393
- Devyn, don't do this, please.

27:42.395 --> 27:44.728
- I have to.

27:44.730 --> 27:46.230
- Why?

27:46.232 --> 27:48.198
- I don't want to hurt you.

27:50.002 --> 27:51.235
- Devyn, if you pull
that trigger,

27:51.237 --> 27:54.371
I won't recover
for the rest of my life.

27:54.373 --> 27:55.673
All right?

27:55.675 --> 27:57.141
If you don't want to hurt me,

27:57.143 --> 28:00.277
you put the gun down,
we walk out of here,

28:00.279 --> 28:02.880
and things will get better,
I promise you, all right?

28:04.450 --> 28:06.216
You give me the gun.

28:06.218 --> 28:10.020
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:10.022 --> 28:12.056
Devyn, give me the gun.

28:12.058 --> 28:16.427
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:16.429 --> 28:18.462
If you love me,

28:18.464 --> 28:20.831
you will give me the gun.

28:20.833 --> 28:22.399
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:22.401 --> 28:24.168
Give it to me.

28:24.170 --> 28:31.141
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:34.346 --> 28:37.314
[sobbing]

28:40.352 --> 28:43.487
You're so stupid.

28:43.489 --> 28:45.456
Don't you ever scare me
like that again.

28:45.458 --> 28:49.059
[sobbing]

28:49.061 --> 28:50.027
- I love you so much.

28:50.029 --> 28:52.863
- [sobbing]

28:52.865 --> 28:56.433
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:56.435 --> 28:58.235
- Stop right there!
- Drop the weapons.

28:58.237 --> 28:59.503
- All right, bitches,
drop them!

28:59.505 --> 29:01.205
- I said drop it!

29:01.207 --> 29:02.239
- Drop it!

29:02.241 --> 29:04.441
Drop it!
- Hey, hey!

29:06.345 --> 29:08.912
- You stole our food.
- I didn't know it was yours.

29:08.914 --> 29:11.915
- I don't care.
- Where are the others?

29:11.917 --> 29:13.217
- What others?
- The ones who were there

29:13.219 --> 29:15.219
when my friend died.
- What friend?

29:15.221 --> 29:17.454
- Tell us, or studly
here gets it.

29:17.456 --> 29:23.460
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:25.197 --> 29:27.865
<i> [tense music]</i>

29:27.867 --> 29:30.434
- Let us go and you won't die.
- Oh, you got that backwards.

29:30.436 --> 29:34.037
- We're here with soldiers.
Better trained than you.

29:34.039 --> 29:35.105
We don't meet them in
15 minutes,

29:35.107 --> 29:36.507
they're gonna blow
your heads off.

29:36.509 --> 29:39.777
- Bullshit.

29:39.779 --> 29:41.211
- They're Army Rangers.
They're trained to track.

29:41.213 --> 29:42.479
You're wearing
their favorite color.

29:42.481 --> 29:44.481
I'm your only way out.

29:44.483 --> 29:46.183
Here's the deal.
You take us to the truck.

29:46.185 --> 29:48.552
We let you live.

29:54.193 --> 29:55.826
We split the food.

29:55.828 --> 30:02.566
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:10.976 --> 30:13.076
- I need to read your work.
- Too late.

30:13.078 --> 30:16.313
Yesterday I decided I didn't
have the guts to die in lava,

30:16.315 --> 30:18.081
so you know what I did?

30:18.083 --> 30:20.250
I took a little drive into town,

30:20.252 --> 30:22.553
went to the local
hardware store,

30:22.555 --> 30:24.588
liberated some high explosives,

30:24.590 --> 30:26.207
and the whole building is wired.

30:26.208 --> 30:27.825
I'm gonna die with my work.
- Why would you do that?

30:27.827 --> 30:28.892
Why wouldn't you want
to save people?

30:28.894 --> 30:30.928
- Save, save, save?

30:30.930 --> 30:32.429
No one is saved, asshole.

30:32.431 --> 30:34.865
It's the apocalypse.
You think things are bad now?

30:34.867 --> 30:37.534
They're just gonna get much,
much worse.

30:37.536 --> 30:39.303
I'm gonna die right here.

30:39.305 --> 30:42.105
- Gloria, it's not too late.
- Thankfully, it is too late.

30:42.107 --> 30:44.274
- Listen, I just--I need to know
how you did that.

30:44.276 --> 30:45.442
I need to know
how you predicted that.

30:45.444 --> 30:46.610
- I don't know.

30:46.612 --> 30:48.178
- I need to know
what process you used.

30:48.180 --> 30:49.880
- I don't have a method.

30:49.882 --> 30:52.049
All of a sudden
I just knew everything.

30:52.051 --> 30:53.417
- Why?

30:53.419 --> 30:55.052
- You have to know why?

30:55.054 --> 30:56.887
- Yes, of course, of course!

30:59.925 --> 31:01.859
- I think I'm part of the wave.

31:01.861 --> 31:06.330
I think the wave is using me,
and I can't stand myself.

31:08.334 --> 31:12.369
- All right, so if there's
a cause then it's not random,

31:12.371 --> 31:13.937
then there's a purpose,

31:13.939 --> 31:15.906
and then life has meaning,
and then there's--

31:15.908 --> 31:18.909
- Of course life has meaning.
It's just not good.

31:23.482 --> 31:26.049
All right,
you want me to help you?

31:26.051 --> 31:30.420
There's--there's a piece
of my research out there.

31:30.422 --> 31:34.258
It's in a nice,
little box...

31:34.260 --> 31:35.993
- Right.
- In plain sight.

31:35.995 --> 31:38.262
You find it.
You understand it.

31:38.264 --> 31:39.963
Maybe it helps you.

31:39.965 --> 31:43.467
And you have one minute
till the building blows up.

31:43.469 --> 31:44.468
- I don't believe you.

31:44.470 --> 31:46.103
- 58 seconds.

31:48.440 --> 31:50.040
56 seconds.

31:50.042 --> 31:52.509
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:52.511 --> 31:54.444
You I'm gonna miss.

31:55.981 --> 31:56.980
[gun cocks]

31:58.317 --> 32:00.918
- We had a deal.

32:00.920 --> 32:02.119
- I don't hear any soldiers.

32:02.121 --> 32:04.187
- That's why they train.

32:04.189 --> 32:05.622
- Think you can die quietly?

32:05.624 --> 32:09.026
- Well, that's pretty cocky
for a slack-ass, barnyard bitch.

32:09.028 --> 32:10.928
[grunts]

32:10.930 --> 32:11.995
[gunfire]

32:11.997 --> 32:13.463
- Back off, soldier boy.

32:13.465 --> 32:15.365
<i> [tense music ]</i>

32:15.367 --> 32:16.500
- [grunts]
- Ow!

32:16.502 --> 32:18.502
- [grunts]

32:18.504 --> 32:20.203
[both grunt]

32:20.205 --> 32:24.174
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:24.176 --> 32:25.642
- You know how this goes.

32:30.950 --> 32:32.382
Here's the deal.

32:32.384 --> 32:33.483
I'll let you keep the food

32:33.485 --> 32:35.252
if you tell me
where the others are.

32:35.254 --> 32:38.522
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:38.524 --> 32:42.259
- Clock's ticking, Josh.

32:42.261 --> 32:44.695
Getting warmer.

32:44.697 --> 32:46.997
- Computer cards.

32:46.999 --> 32:49.967
- Tick, tick, tick.

32:49.969 --> 32:50.968
- [yells]

32:50.970 --> 32:52.002
[groans]

32:52.004 --> 32:54.037
- Time's a-wasting.

32:54.039 --> 32:57.541
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:57.543 --> 33:00.510
[watch beeping]

33:00.512 --> 33:02.746
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:02.748 --> 33:04.414
[watch continues beeping]

33:04.416 --> 33:06.383
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:06.385 --> 33:08.418
- I want my daughter.
- What daughter?

33:08.420 --> 33:11.355
- The girl you saw
with the soldier.

33:11.357 --> 33:13.991
- Oh, hell.
[laughs]

33:13.993 --> 33:18.028
We offed that tasty little slice
and her boyfriend.

33:18.030 --> 33:19.029
[gunshot]

33:19.031 --> 33:20.063
[yells]

33:20.065 --> 33:22.699
- Oh, no, please, no!

33:22.701 --> 33:23.734
[gunshot]

33:23.736 --> 33:25.002
- No!
Please, God.

33:25.003 --> 33:26.269
- Where's my daughter?
- Please, please, please, no!

33:26.271 --> 33:27.270
- [yells]

33:27.272 --> 33:29.172
[gunfire]

33:29.174 --> 33:30.507
- You son of a bitch.

33:30.509 --> 33:32.109
[gunfire]

33:32.111 --> 33:33.477
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:33.479 --> 33:36.079
- Mom.

33:36.081 --> 33:39.116
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

33:39.118 --> 33:40.117
- Dana.

33:40.119 --> 33:42.119
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:42.121 --> 33:44.388
- What have you done?

33:44.390 --> 33:46.623
- They told me you were dead.

33:46.625 --> 33:48.759
- So you killed them?

33:48.761 --> 33:50.127
- Honey.

33:50.129 --> 33:51.728
- Don't touch me.

33:51.730 --> 33:54.097
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:54.099 --> 33:55.098
Who are you?

33:55.100 --> 34:02.072
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:03.409 --> 34:05.308
[knocking on door]

34:05.310 --> 34:06.576
- It's me.

34:06.578 --> 34:07.577
Open up.

34:07.579 --> 34:08.745
- Dad?

34:10.649 --> 34:11.715
- It's Dad.

34:11.717 --> 34:13.450
- Why didn't you
bring your keys?

34:13.452 --> 34:15.285
I was getting worried.
Did you find the papers?

34:15.287 --> 34:16.620
And where's Jane?

34:16.622 --> 34:18.755
Sorry I'm cranky.
I've had a shitty day.

34:21.360 --> 34:24.227
Dad.

34:24.229 --> 34:26.396
Dad.

34:26.398 --> 34:27.831
[grunts]

34:27.833 --> 34:29.399
Dad!
- [yells]

34:29.401 --> 34:30.367
- [growling]
- Dad!

34:30.369 --> 34:31.368
Dad, don't!

34:31.370 --> 34:32.402
- [growls]

34:32.404 --> 34:33.603
- [grunts]
Daddy!

34:33.605 --> 34:35.572
Daddy don't do it!
Please!

34:35.574 --> 34:37.107
Don't!

34:37.109 --> 34:39.142
Don't!
- [growls]

34:39.144 --> 34:41.812
- [screaming]
- [growling]

34:43.615 --> 34:45.515
- Brianna!

34:45.517 --> 34:46.550
Are you okay?

34:46.552 --> 34:48.585
<i> [tense music]</i>

34:48.587 --> 34:50.253
You're safe now.
- It wasn't him.

34:50.255 --> 34:51.521
It wasn't him.
- You're safe now.

34:51.523 --> 34:52.689
- It wasn't him.

34:52.691 --> 34:55.625
[sobbing]

35:02.201 --> 35:03.667
- There's no bomb, huh?

35:03.669 --> 35:05.102
- I'm a kidder.

35:05.104 --> 35:06.436
- Mm.

35:06.438 --> 35:10.474
- But I'm--I'm not kidding
about being afraid.

35:10.476 --> 35:12.342
I am afraid of volcanoes.

35:12.344 --> 35:14.277
I'm afraid of bombs.

35:14.279 --> 35:16.613
So I want you to do it.

35:16.615 --> 35:17.681
You have to kill me.

35:17.683 --> 35:19.716
- I'm not gonna kill you.

35:19.718 --> 35:20.817
- Why not?

35:20.819 --> 35:22.285
You killed me once already.

35:22.287 --> 35:23.653
You're good at it.

35:23.655 --> 35:25.572
- I don't know
what you're talking about.

35:25.573 --> 35:27.490
- You know, when you
and your little boyfriends

35:27.493 --> 35:31.394
in academia were done with me,
I couldn't get a job anywhere.

35:32.831 --> 35:35.365
I end up
at Memphis Pacific College.

35:35.367 --> 35:37.567
Are you kidding me?

35:37.569 --> 35:39.603
Memphis is nowhere
near the Pacific.

35:39.605 --> 35:43.206
I look like an idiot.
I should have gone to Princeton.

35:43.208 --> 35:44.908
I should have been famous.

35:44.910 --> 35:46.209
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:46.211 --> 35:49.179
I'm the one who knew everything,

35:49.181 --> 35:51.331
and look where I end up:

35:51.332 --> 35:53.482
in this shithole
with no publications,

35:53.485 --> 35:56.353
and no kids

35:56.355 --> 35:57.354
and no hope.

35:57.356 --> 36:00.423
So you owe me.

36:00.425 --> 36:05.262
Okay, just do it,

36:05.264 --> 36:06.630
and take the computer cards.

36:06.632 --> 36:09.299
They're all you need
to understand this whole thing.

36:09.301 --> 36:10.800
Now shoot me.

36:10.802 --> 36:13.570
- Well, I can't use the computer
cards without a reader.

36:13.572 --> 36:15.639
- Wait a second.

36:15.641 --> 36:18.375
[clears throat]

36:18.377 --> 36:19.843
[sighs]

36:19.845 --> 36:26.850
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:26.852 --> 36:29.286
Shoot me.

36:29.288 --> 36:31.755
- I'm not gonna shoot you.

36:31.757 --> 36:33.523
Come with me.

36:33.525 --> 36:34.791
- Shoot me.
- Join us.

36:34.793 --> 36:36.293
We have a room.
- Just shoot me.

36:36.295 --> 36:37.694
- I can make you safe.
- Shoot me, Josh.

36:37.696 --> 36:39.329
- You can travel with us.
- Just shoot me!

36:39.331 --> 36:40.864
- I'm not gonna shoot you!

36:40.866 --> 36:42.399
[gunshot]

36:42.401 --> 36:43.366
- [laughing]
Oh.

36:43.368 --> 36:44.367
Wow.

36:44.369 --> 36:47.404
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:47.406 --> 36:48.872
[breathing raggedly]

36:48.874 --> 36:49.906
Thank you.

36:49.908 --> 36:53.710
[breathing raggedly]

36:53.712 --> 36:57.214
- When someone asks you to do
that, you do it, okay?

36:57.216 --> 36:58.481
The thing about end of times

36:58.483 --> 37:00.217
is that people know
what they want.

37:00.219 --> 37:06.957
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:08.627 --> 37:12.295
- Listen to the voices
in the night, Josh.

37:12.297 --> 37:16.233
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:44.963 --> 37:46.663
- What's wrong?.

37:48.000 --> 37:49.599
- Big day, Dad.

37:49.601 --> 37:51.534
[sighs]

37:51.536 --> 37:53.536
Big day.

38:11.657 --> 38:13.623
- Hi.
What happened?

38:13.625 --> 38:16.026
- We got what we needed.

38:16.028 --> 38:17.494
- And the bodies on the ground?

38:17.496 --> 38:19.362
- They got what they needed.

38:19.364 --> 38:21.898
- Yeah, they would have killed
us if we hadn't made a move.

38:25.604 --> 38:26.870
- Okay.

38:28.907 --> 38:30.640
- Matt, you got to tell him.

38:32.311 --> 38:35.312
- They were GRs.
The worst I've seen.

38:35.314 --> 38:38.014
They threatened us.
They taunted Mom.

38:38.016 --> 38:40.450
I mean, they told
her Dana was dead.

38:40.452 --> 38:42.786
- That's--that's gonna do it.

38:44.323 --> 38:47.924
- The last one she shot
over and over.

38:47.926 --> 38:50.393
It must have been 20 times.
She just lost it.

38:55.600 --> 38:57.534
I'm sorry.
- No, it's my fault.

38:57.536 --> 38:58.819
I should have been around here.

38:58.820 --> 39:00.103
There's nothing you could
have done about it, so...

39:02.474 --> 39:03.606
What about Dana?

39:05.711 --> 39:06.943
- She fought off a Jubokko.

39:11.850 --> 39:13.817
- Well, then she gets to smoke.

39:16.421 --> 39:19.556
- [cackling]

39:19.558 --> 39:21.558
- What's going on with Devyn?
- I'll handle it.

39:21.560 --> 39:22.559
- Hoo, hoo, hoo!

39:22.561 --> 39:23.660
[cackling]

39:23.662 --> 39:25.695
- Dev!
Dev, stop.

39:28.700 --> 39:31.601
I saw it.
- Stay away from me.

39:31.603 --> 39:33.803
- I saw the skinwalker.

39:33.805 --> 39:36.439
- Then you know
I'm going to kill you.

39:38.710 --> 39:40.610
If you saw it, you know.

39:40.612 --> 39:42.112
You know it's true.

39:44.850 --> 39:46.383
- No, you won't.

39:46.385 --> 39:47.851
You don't hurt
the people you love.

39:47.853 --> 39:49.753
- But you don't love me.

39:49.755 --> 39:52.422
<i> [somber music]</i>

39:52.424 --> 39:53.823
- [growls]

39:53.825 --> 39:55.725
- Look at me.

39:55.727 --> 39:57.727
Look at me.

39:57.729 --> 40:02.832
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:02.834 --> 40:05.635
I love you, okay?

40:05.637 --> 40:07.804
I mean it, I do, but you--

40:07.806 --> 40:10.039
you cannot flip out on me,
all right?

40:10.041 --> 40:11.574
They will kill you.

40:11.576 --> 40:13.009
You have to understand that.

40:13.011 --> 40:14.677
You won't last.

40:14.679 --> 40:16.413
- I tried to fight it, Brianna.

40:16.415 --> 40:17.647
I have, and I can't anymore.

40:17.649 --> 40:19.082
- Yes, you can, Devyn.

40:19.084 --> 40:21.651
You can fight it.
Love is stronger than anything.

40:21.653 --> 40:23.653
- It's not stronger than this.

40:23.655 --> 40:30.627
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:31.830 --> 40:35.198
- You're a good person, okay?

40:35.200 --> 40:36.633
I'm gonna help you.

40:36.635 --> 40:41.938
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:41.940 --> 40:44.174
- I love you so much.

40:44.176 --> 40:46.676
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:46.678 --> 40:49.913
He's making me do this because
he knows how much I love you.

40:49.915 --> 40:55.118
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:55.120 --> 40:58.087
[growling]

40:58.089 --> 41:02.158
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:02.160 --> 41:03.760
[in deep voice]
I won't let you have the boy.

41:03.762 --> 41:05.562
- Devyn, no.
Please!

41:05.564 --> 41:06.629
Please.

41:06.631 --> 41:08.498
- Hey, hey!
- [growls]

41:08.500 --> 41:09.499
- Devyn, don't!
Please!

41:09.501 --> 41:10.500
Please don't do it!

41:10.502 --> 41:12.168
Please!
Please!

41:12.170 --> 41:14.637
Devyn!

41:14.639 --> 41:15.805
Please.

41:15.807 --> 41:16.840
Please don't do this.

41:16.842 --> 41:17.974
Devyn don't do this, please.

41:17.976 --> 41:19.576
- You were right.

41:19.578 --> 41:21.144
Love is stronger, Brianna.

41:21.146 --> 41:22.512
- [whispering]
Please.

41:22.514 --> 41:23.513
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:23.515 --> 41:24.547
[gunshot]

41:24.549 --> 41:26.683
[no audible dialogue]

41:26.685 --> 41:33.656
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:18.603 --> 42:21.604
[rumbling]

42:21.606 --> 42:28.545
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:32.050 --> 42:35.018
<i> [intense music]</i>

42:35.020 --> 42:41.991
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
